  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/deliveroo/4b60f14b-0bc1-44cc-a7da-a1ce76f8d248/application",
    "company": "Deliveroo",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "b9d505e78d89e9e5",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "OPERATIONS STRATEGY MANAGER - NEW VERTICALS\n\nJoin us in our mission to transform the way people shop and eat, where impact, innovation, and growth drives everything we do. Our Commercial team sits at the centre of Deliveroo’s marketplace—shaping how we serve restaurants, grocers, and new verticals worldwide. From negotiating key partnerships to unlocking new revenue streams and crafting data-led growth strategies, we take on big challenges that move the business forward. If you thrive in fast-paced, commercial environments and want to influence the future of a global brand—this is the team for you.\n\nWe’re looking for an Operations Strategy Manager - New verticals to join our London team. In this role, you’ll help us develop and scale strategic initiatives that drive operational excellence, ensuring we maximise business profitability while delivering the best possible experience to our customers.\n\nGet to know our Operations https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/operations/ team — what drives us, how we work, and what you can expect.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BE DOING\n\nYou’ll be joining the Quality and Cost team within the New Verticals Strategy \u0026 Operations function. We are responsible for the strategy that drives service quality and cost-control, balancing high-impact strategic problem-solving with the real-world execution of our ideas.\n\nHere’s what your day-to-day might look like:\n\n - Lead Strategic Initiatives: Design and implement operational frameworks that improve quality metrics and cost efficiency across our grocery and retail segments.\n\n - Drive Product Go-To-Market: Lead the execution of go-to-market processes for new partner product features, ensuring smooth launches and scalable adoption.\n\n - Performance Management: Own the target-setting and OKR process for New Verticals, providing regular performance reporting through weekly and monthly business reviews.\n\n - Operational Problem Solving: Conduct deep-dive analyses to identify why KPIs might be off-track and pull the necessary levers to bring performance back to standard.\n\n - Standardise Excellence: Develop scalable Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), training programmes, and tools that enable local teams to execute the central strategy effectively.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED TO THRIVE\n\nEssential\n\n - Operational Excellence: Significant experience (3+ years) in a grocery or retail environment with a focus on driving operational improvement plans.\n\n - Analytical Rigour: A strong quantitative toolkit (Excel) and the ability to conduct 80/20 analysis to draw out actionable insights from complex data.\n\n - Influential Communication: Proven ability to persuade senior stakeholders and galvanise action across cross-functional teams like Commercial, Product, and Legal.\n\n - Strategic Execution: A unique blend of high-level strategic thinking and a \"roll-up-your-sleeves\" approach to on-the-ground operational implementation.\n\n - Decisiveness: Comfort making fast, data-informed decisions in ambiguous, fast-paced environments.\n\nNice to Have\n\n - A mix of site-level operations and central strategy implementation experience.\n\n - Experience driving strategic priorities across global, remote teams.\n\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n🔧 Make a visible impact every day\n\nYour work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment\n\nWork close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n🧠 Build a career, not just a role\n\nStretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture\n\nCollaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/how-we-hire/.\n\n\nOUR GLOBAL STRUCTURE\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\n\nDIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSION\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
